</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td><strong>Nigeria</strong></td>
<td>Islamic shari'a courts, northern region</td>
<td>Muslim personal law, Maliki school; penal law</td>
<td><p><a href="https://www.constituteproject.org/constitution/Nigeria_1999?lang=en">Const.1999</a> (as amended to 2011 via World Constitutions Illustrated (fee based)- Shari'a court of appeal in each state; final unless federal constitutional questions arise; problem of separate Shari'a penal codes 12 states in north such as Zamfara, enforced by separate courts;</p>
